				\begin{document}$${\sigma }_{d}=\frac{1}{2A}({E}_{slab}-{E}_{bulk})$$\end{document}where A is a constant, Eslab and Ebulk are the total energy of a surface slab and of the corresponding bulk PbBr2, respectively. The so-defined detachment energy, σd, was derived from the equation above by using density functional theory (DFT) as the total energy of a surface slab before structural relaxation (see Methods section). After structural relaxation the surface formation energy, σf, should be used instead. This is calculated from the same equation by using the total energy of the fully-relaxed surface slab33.
